solution.p:
We use the FOIL technique: First Outside Inside Last  \begin{aligned}
              \left({5r-10}\right)({5r+10})\amp ={25r^{2}+50r-50r-100}\\
                                \amp ={25r^{2}-100}
      \end{aligned}

Alternatively, we might observe that this is the product of the sum and difference of two terms, in which case we may use the formula (a-b)(a+b)=a^2-b^2 and write \begin{aligned}
              \left({5r-10}\right)({5r+10})\amp =(5r)^2-10^2\\
                                \amp ={25r^{2}-100}
      \end{aligned} which is the same result we obtained using the FOIL method.
